history.heading: A “symmetric algorithm” employing a key length in excess of 56-bits; or
history.title: A “symmetric algorithm” employing a key length in excess of 56-bits; or

supplement.heading: Supplement No. 1 to Part 774 - The Commerce Control List

breadcrumbs: 5A002 “Information security” systems, equipment and “components,” as follows (see List of Items Controlled).
Systems, equipment and components, for cryptographic “information security,” as follows:

Designed or modified to use “cryptography” employing digital techniques performing any cryptographic function other than authentication, digital signature, or execution of copy-protected “software,” and having any of the following:
history.text:
A “symmetric algorithm” employing a key length in excess of 56-bits; or
Technical Note: In Category 5 - Part 2, parity bits are not included in the key length.
